b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48484.htm)  [Next](sbe48486.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n38\\. And there is the promotion (of knowledge) through special acts (of duty).\n\np. 705\n\nThe above conclusion is founded not only on Reasoning and Sm _ri_ ti; but\nScripture even directly states that knowledge is benefited by practices not\nexclusively prescribed for the a _s_ ramas, 'By penance, abstinence, faith,\nand knowledge he is to seek the Self (Pr. Up. I, 10).\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 39. But better than that is the other also on account of an inferential\nmark](sbe48486.htm)\n\n"